<HEAD>Life Support Pulled From Texas Infant With Almost No Brain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOMA LINDA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> infant born with almost no brain was taken off life-support equipment that was intended to help preserve her tiny heart and other organs for transplantation, a doctor said Saturday. `` Baby <PERSON> Evelyn </PERSON> continues to breathe on her own, but shows signs of gradual deterioration,'' Dr. <PERSON> Joyce </PERSON> <PERSON> Peabody </PERSON>, chief of neonatology at <ORGANIZATION> Loma </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Linda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, said in a statement late Saturday. <PERSON> Evelyn </PERSON> <PERSON> Keys </PERSON> was born with a fatal genetic birth defect known as anencephaly, in which much of the upper brain and skull are missing. <PERSON> Loma </PERSON> <PERSON> Linda </PERSON> has developed the nation's first guidelines using such infants as organ donors. However, little <PERSON> Evelyn </PERSON> never met the hospital's criteria for brain-death since she was born seven days ago, and machine-assisted breathing was stopped Saturday, with her parents' consent, <ORGANIZATION> Peabody </ORGANIZATION> said. Although three newborns needing healthy livers had been identified during the week, the likelihood of a vital organ transplant dropped to nil, hospital spokesman <PERSON> Anita </PERSON> <PERSON> Rockwell </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Baby </PERSON> <PERSON> Evelyn </PERSON> will be allowed to die naturally, she said. `` It is highly unlikely that she will be able to donate organs such as liver and heart, because without continuation of assisted breathing, oxygen deprivation of these organs will occur prior to her death,'' Ms. <PERSON> Rockwell </PERSON> said. Details about the potential liver recipients were n't disclosed, but Ms. <PERSON> Rockwell </PERSON> said they were n't at <LOCATION> Loma </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Linda </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Evelyn </PERSON> was born Feb. 20 in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION