 <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Zhang </PERSON> <PERSON> Jiashu </PERSON>, bishop of <LOCATION> Shanghai </LOCATION> under <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s independent <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION>, has died at the age of 96, the official <ORGANIZATION> Xinhua </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> reported Sunday. Mass was said Saturday for <PERSON> Zhang </PERSON>, who died Thursday, at the <LOCATION> Xujiahui </LOCATION> Cathedral in <LOCATION> Shanghai </LOCATION>, the city's largest, the agency said. Among those attending where <PERSON> Zong </PERSON> <PERSON> Huaide </PERSON>, bishop of <LOCATION> Jinan </LOCATION> diocese and chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> China </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patriotic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>. The `` Patriotic'' <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> broke with the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> in 1957 after accusing <LOCATION> Rome </LOCATION> of interfering in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s internal affairs The church claims more than 3 million followers in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Xinhua </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Zhang </PERSON> studied in <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> for 10 years before returning to <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> in 1924. In 1960, he was elected bishop of the <LOCATION> Shanghai </LOCATION> diocese, which has an estimated 100,000 parishioners and about 20 churches. The report said he was vice chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> China </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patriotic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>, director of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administrative </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATIO