 the civil war that followed. Government forces are backed by some 40,000 Cuban troops and more than 1,000 Soviet military advisers. Also Sunday, <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> announced that two of its soldiers were killed in <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>. The military statement said the troops were slain Thursday by `` indirect enemy fire.'' <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> announced in November that it had intervened militarily in southern <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION> on behalf of <ORGANIZATION> UNITA </ORGANIZATION>. A month later <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> said it had begun to withdraw its troops, but it remains engaged in the fighting. <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> has announced the deaths of more than 30 South African military personnel since November, but has not disclosed the extent of its involvement. <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION> claims 9,000 South African troopers are in <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>.
